article.headline: UMKC 69, Centenary 63
article.story: KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Quinton Day scored 27 points to lead Missouri-Kansas City to a 69-63 win over Centenary on Saturday night. Day, who had 16 points in the second half, made four free throws in the last 23 seconds to cement the victory. The Kangaroos (6-7, 3-1 Mid-Continent) took command of the game in the second half after leading only 31-30 at halftime. UMKC led by 10 points three times in the second half, the last at 61-51 on a basket by Kyle Spears with 5:11 left. The Gents (2-11, 0-3) lost their sixth consecutive game. They were able to get within three when Xavier Burnette's 3-point shot made it 65-62 with 26 seconds left, but Day followed with two free throws. Dee Ayuba had 19 points and Brent Stephens added 10 for UMKC, and Ayuba and Day had six rebounds each to lead UMKC. Burnette and Bryan Baumann led the Gents with 11 each and Larry Logan had eight rebounds.
